		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">The Fifteen Decisive Battles of the World</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><i><b>The Fifteen Decisive Battles of the World: from Marathon to Waterloo</b></i> is a <a href="/wiki/Book" title="Book">book</a> written by Sir <a href="/wiki/Edward_Shepherd_Creasy" title="Edward Shepherd Creasy">Edward Shepherd Creasy</a> and published in 1851. This book tells the story of the fifteen <a href="/wiki/Battle" title="Battle">military engagements</a> (from Marathon to Waterloo) which, according to the author, had a <a href="/wiki/Macro-historical" title="Macro-historical">significant impact on world history</a>.</p>
